Romania Doesn’t Rule Out Bank Capital Outflows, Xinhua Reports

-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 
2011-07-21T07:19:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/romania-doesn-t-rule-out-bank-capital-outflows-xinhua-reports.html
Romania ’s central bank doesn’t rule
out bank capital outflows as the European debt crisis threatens
international lenders that control 90 percent of the domestic
market, Governor Mugur Isarescu told Xinhua News Agency.  The Banca Nationala a Romaniei is monitoring possible
capital withdrawals and is ready to react to any contagion
through the “thin” capital channel, Isarescu told the Chinese
news service in an interview on July 19. Such moves which won’t
create market disruptions, he told Xinhua.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  